&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;CaptiveAire is hiring HVAC and duct Installers for our new self-performing install crew, delivering turnkey HVAC installations for national accounts — rooftop units, supply/return/exhaust duct, low-voltage controls, and full system change-outs — to CaptiveAire’s quality standard. Extensive travel is required.This role will report to the Field Engineer/Install Team Lead. The opportunity to be a founding member of CaptiveAire’s first install crew and grow with the program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Work for Captive-Aire?&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nation’s leading manufacturer of commercial kitchen ventilation systems, and now offering a complete solution of fans, heaters, ductwork and HVAC equipment.  Our primary purpose is to provide fully integrated, sustainable HVAC Systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leader in the industry for over 40 years with innovative technologies, unmatched service, competitive pricing, and rapid lead times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mission: to provide the highest quality products and service to our users at the lowest possible price&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong commitment to the development of our employees, including continuous education opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn more about CaptiveAire and our products &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.captiveaire.com/video-library/&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;here&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practice 100% Safe work 100% of the time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install CaptiveAire HVAC equipment — RTUs, ductwork, exhaust fans, and supporting ancillary products — and execute full RTU change-outs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install HVAC low voltage + space HMI’s.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read and interpret blueprints, submittals, and mechanical drawings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow CaptiveAire installation standards on every job — spreader-bar lifts, minimal deck cutouts, CAS-supplied gasket with surplus on hand, and a clean, safe, organized jobsite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with the Installation Manager and field teams to keep installs on schedule and on spec.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mechanical aptitude, a strong work ethic, reliability, and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-5yrs experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to travel to jobsites. Travel across the US is 100% covered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver’s license and clean driving record.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HVAC field/install experience is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;preferred but not required&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for a strong candidate — we will train the trade onto the right attitude and skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commercial HVAC installation experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refrigeration piping and brazing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EPA Certification (or willingness to obtain).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building Automation Systems (BAS) / controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OSHA 10/30; commissioning and air-balancing experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
